  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong>, then<strong> </strong>top, tail, and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely (no need to peel!)</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s] </strong>in half lengthways, then wash to remove any grit from between the leaves then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Strip your <strong>thyme</strong> leaves from the stems, chop finely and discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1649848574789-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1649848574789-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1649848574789-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1649848574789-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1649848574789-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>sliced leek</strong> and <strong>diced carrot </strong>along with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min until beginning to soften</p><p>Crumble your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into rough chunks</p><p>Once soft, add your <strong>pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>crumbled mushrooms </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1649848578670-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1649848578670-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1649848578670-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1649848578670-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1649848578670-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[350ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]<strong> </span>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Once the pork is cooked, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped thyme </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> tomato stock </strong>and cook for 5-7 min or until slightly thickened – this is your<strong> pork ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1649848583376-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1649848583376-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1649848583376-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1649848583376-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1649848583376-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, melt 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[22g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add your<strong> fennel seeds</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[22g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1649848588419-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1649848588419-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1649848588419-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1649848588419-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1649848588419-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Gradually add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span><strong> water </strong>to the <strong>roux </strong>and whisk for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Remove the pot from the heat, season with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir through <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>cheddar </strong>– this is your<strong> cheesy fennel béchamel</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1724339315918-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
